key_points: Human remains found in Teton County, Wyoming, match the description of missing 22-year-old Gabby Petito.
FBI's full forensic identification is pending to confirm the identity of the remains.
The cause of death has not been determined, as stated by FBI Denver's supervisory senior resident agent, Charles Jones.
Search efforts were conducted in the Spread Creek Dispersed Camping Area and Bridger-Teton National Forest.
Authorities in Florida are searching for Petito's fiancé, Brian Laundrie, whose whereabouts are unknown.
Petito was reported missing on September 11, after a road trip with Laundrie, who returned home without her on September 1.
Laundrie is not currently wanted for a crime, but his sudden disappearance has prompted extensive search efforts.
The search for Laundrie in Carlton Reserve involved drones, bloodhounds, and spanned roughly 25,000 acres.
North Port police spokesperson Josh Taylor commented on the ongoing investigations and search efforts.
Laundrie family attorney Steven Bertolino and Petito family attorney Richard Stafford have provided statements on the situation.
spokespersons: Charles Jones (FBI Denver's supervisory senior resident agent)
